    body: "The Living Rosary (Le Rosaire Vivant) was founded by Blessed Pauline Jaricot in Lyon, France, in 1826. A group of fifteen members (now twenty, since the addition of the Luminous Mysteries) each takes responsibility for one specific mystery and prays that single decade every day. Together, the circle completes the entire Rosary daily. Members are typically assigned their mystery by lot and rotate monthly. The association spread rapidly and received papal approval. Pauline Jaricot saw the Living Rosary as both a school of prayer for those who found the full Rosary too demanding and a means of building spiritual solidarity among members who pray for one another's intentions.",
