    oneLiner: "Eucharistic adoration conducted during nighttime hours in a spirit of reparation and keeping watch with Christ.",
    body: "Night Adoration is a form of Eucharistic devotion in which the faithful spend hours of the night before the exposed Blessed Sacrament, echoing Christ's invitation to the Apostles in Gethsemane: 'Could you not watch one hour with me?' (Matthew 26:40). The Nocturnal Adoration Society, founded in Rome in 1810 and spread worldwide, organizes men into bands that take turns adoring through the night on a rotating schedule. Night adoration carries a particular spirit of reparation for sins committed under cover of darkness and intercession for sinners. Some communities practice it monthly, gathering after evening and remaining until morning Mass. The silence and sacrifice of lost sleep give this devotion its distinctive penitential character.",
