    body: "The Red Scapular of the Passion was revealed to Sister Apolline Andriveau, a Daughter of Charity of St. Vincent de Paul, in 1846. On one panel it bears an image of Christ on the Cross with the instruments of the Passion and the inscription 'Holy Passion of Our Lord Jesus Christ, save us.' On the other side, it shows the Sacred Hearts of Jesus and Mary with the inscription 'Sacred Hearts of Jesus and Mary, protect us.' Approved by Pope Pius IX in 1847, it was originally restricted to the Vincentian family but later extended to all the faithful. Those who wear it are promised an increase in faith, hope, and charity, and are encouraged to meditate on the Passion every Friday. The red color symbolizes the Blood of Christ shed for the salvation of the world.",
