    tags: ["First Fridays", "Sacred Heart", "promises", "Communion", "Margaret Mary"],
    oneLiner: "The promise of Christ to St. Margaret Mary that those who receive Communion on nine consecutive First Fridays will receive the grace of final repentance.",
    body: "The Nine First Fridays devotion is based on the twelfth and greatest of the Twelve Promises of the Sacred Heart given to St. Margaret Mary Alacoque: 'I promise you in the excessive mercy of My Heart that My all-powerful love will grant to all those who receive Holy Communion on the First Friday of nine consecutive months the grace of final repentance; they shall not die in My disgrace nor without receiving their sacraments. My divine Heart shall be their safe refuge in this last moment.' The practice requires receiving Holy Communion in a state of grace on the First Friday of each month for nine consecutive months, with the intention of honoring the Sacred Heart and making reparation for sins. If a month is missed, the count begins again. Theologians note that this promise presupposes the dispositions of genuine devotion, not a mechanical guarantee. The devotion has been practiced by millions of Catholics since the 17th century and is closely linked to the broader Sacred Heart devotion.",
