    oneLiner: "The practice of receiving Holy Communion with the specific intention of making amends for sins committed against the Sacred Heart of Jesus or the Immaculate Heart of Mary.",
    body: "A Communion of Reparation is the reception of the Holy Eucharist offered specifically to console the Hearts of Jesus and Mary for the injuries, ingratitude, and sacrilege they suffer from sinners. The practice is rooted in the Sacred Heart revelations to St. Margaret Mary, in which Jesus lamented the coldness and contempt He receives even from consecrated souls, and asked for a 'Communion of reparation' on the First Friday of each month. The Blessed Virgin Mary similarly requested Communions of reparation on First Saturdays at Fatima in 1917, asking that the faithful receive Communion to make amends for blasphemies against her Immaculate Heart. The theological foundation lies in the Communion of Saints: the merits and sufferings of one member can benefit others, and reparation offered to God can satisfy, in a secondary sense, for the offenses of sinners. Making a Communion of reparation requires being in a state of grace and explicitly forming the intention of reparation.",
