    oneLiner: "An association in which members choose a specific hour each day to spiritually keep watch before the Sacred Heart in a spirit of love and reparation.",
    body: "The Guard of Honor of the Sacred Heart was founded in 1863 by Sister Mary of the Sacred Heart Bernaud at the Visitation Monastery in Bourg-en-Bresse, France. Each member selects one hour of the day as their personal 'hour of guard' during which they unite themselves spiritually with the Sacred Heart of Jesus. This does not require stopping all activities; rather, the member offers whatever they are doing during that hour — work, rest, prayer, or suffering — in a spirit of love, praise, and reparation to the Sacred Heart. The association covers all 24 hours of the day, so that at every moment, somewhere in the world, members are keeping watch before the Heart of Jesus, fulfilling His wish at Gethsemane for companions in His agony. The Guard of Honor was enriched with indulgences by Pope Pius IX and aggregated to the Apostleship of Prayer.",
