    oneLiner: "A worldwide Jesuit-founded network of prayer that unites daily offerings with the Pope's monthly intentions through the Sacred Heart of Jesus.",
    body: "The Apostleship of Prayer (now known as the Pope's Worldwide Prayer Network) was founded in 1844 by Jesuit Father Francois-Xavier Gautrelet at the seminary in Vals, France. Young Jesuit scholastics frustrated by their inability to go to the missions were taught to offer their daily prayers, works, and sufferings for the missionary intentions of the Church. The movement spread explosively and now counts tens of millions of members worldwide. Its central practice is the daily Morning Offering, by which members consecrate their day to the Sacred Heart of Jesus for the Holy Father's monthly prayer intentions (one universal and one for evangelization). Pope Francis relaunched and restructured the apostolate in 2014, emphasizing its digital presence and the 'Click to Pray' app. The association is organized in local groups, and members participate in First Friday devotions and monthly days of recollection.",
