    oneLiner: "The daily practice of praying the Rosary together as a family, popularized by Father Patrick Peyton's motto: 'The family that prays together stays together.'",
    body: "The Family Rosary is the practice of a household gathering daily to pray some or all of the Rosary together. While families have prayed the Rosary together for centuries, the devotion received its most famous promotion through Venerable Father Patrick Peyton, C.S.C. (1909-1992), an Irish-American Holy Cross priest whose worldwide Family Rosary Crusade reached millions through radio, television, and stadium rallies. His slogan, 'The family that prays together stays together,' became one of the most recognized religious phrases of the 20th century. The practice typically involves the family gathering after dinner or before bedtime, with different members leading each decade. Children are encouraged to participate from an early age, even if they can only manage a decade. Many families add intentions for each mystery, pray for deceased family members, and include seasonal devotions. Pope St. John Paul II, in Rosarium Virginis Mariae, strongly encouraged the Family Rosary as a means of combating the crisis of the family.",
