    oneLiner: "Deep meditation on the five Glorious Mysteries of the Rosary, contemplating Christ's triumph and Mary's heavenly glory.",
    body: "The Glorious Mysteries are the final set of the Rosary's traditional fifteen mysteries (prayed on Wednesdays and Sundays), encompassing: the Resurrection of Jesus, the Ascension of Jesus into Heaven, the Descent of the Holy Spirit at Pentecost, the Assumption of Mary into Heaven, and the Coronation of Mary as Queen of Heaven and Earth. These mysteries complete the arc of salvation history begun in the Joyful Mysteries and carried through the Sorrowful Mysteries. Meditation on the Glorious Mysteries draws the faithful beyond the Cross into the reality of Christ's victory over death and the glorification of His Mother. Each mystery opens rich theological territory: the Resurrection as the foundation of Christian faith, the Ascension as Christ's enthronement at the Father's right hand, Pentecost as the birth of the Church, the Assumption as the fulfillment of Mary's unique role, and the Coronation as the revelation of Mary's queenship and the destiny of all the redeemed. Saints recommend praying these mysteries especially during times of suffering, to lift the heart toward the glory that awaits.",
